    "text": "Every time I need to reclaim disk space, I boot up GrandPerspective <http://grandperspectiv.sourceforge.net/>.  One question is whether the size of the circles matters for the activity that you're doing.  Another is whether the relative location of the circles means anything.  As primates, we're used to orientation mattering; so anything like, say, force directed layout is likely to be disorienting.",
